
[1]water-melon

   WATER-MELON, n. [water and melon.] A plant and its fruit, of the genus
   Cucurbita. This plant requires a warm climate to bring it to
   perfection. It also requires a dry, sandy, warm soil, and will not grow
   well in any other. The fruit abounds with a sweetish liquor resembling
   water in color, and the pulp is remarkably rich and delicious.
